<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - ELECTRONICALLY CONTROLLED VARIABLE GEOMETRY TURBOCHARGER (VGT) -
        Removal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26502.2">
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcproc id="s26502.2.1" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, read all safety instructions in the "Safety Information"
                        section of this manual.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the engine has cooled before removing
                        components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or possible death, disconnect the main battery negative terminal
                        before disconnecting or connecting electrical components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not let engine fluids stay on your skin. Clean skin
                        and nails, using a hand cleaner, and wash with soap and water. Wash or discard clothing and rags
                        contaminated with engine fluids.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <note>
                    <para>Engine fluids (oil, fuel and coolant) are a threat to the environment. Recycle or dispose of
                        engine fluids according to local regulations. Never put engine fluids in the trash, on the
                        ground, in sewers or bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650202" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD09/D09125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Disconnection of VGT control valve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT control valve connection</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT control valve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT control valve connector</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT control valve bracket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the engine harness electrical connector from the VGT control valve.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
